==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Estimative
<hw>Es"ti*ma*tive</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[Cf. F.
<ets>estimatif</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Inclined, or able, to
estimate; serving for, or capable of being used in,
estimating.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>We find in animals an <qex>estimative</qex> or judicial
faculty.</q> <rj><qau>Sir M. Hale.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Pertaining to an estimate.</def>
<mark>[R.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Estimator</ent>⟦br⟧
